Per AFP:   The urn bearing Aquino’s ashes will be brought out from the Church by the PSG pall bearers going to family-arranged bus. 2 buses on convoy. Expected to join the convoy is more or less 100 private vehicles.   PNP HPG, MMDA, PSG riders will manage the traffic, provide motorcycle escorts during travel via C5, SLEX to Sucat. PNP chief Gen. Guillermo Eleazar said around 1,000 police officers deployed to secure funeral.  AFP chief Gen. Cirilito Sobejana w/ other military officials awaiting Aquino family at Manila Memorial Park, where they will be escorted to arrival honors area. Urn will be handed to pallbearers, who are all AFP generals.  The urn will be loaded to a hearse for the funeral march to the Aquino mausoleum, which is ~150 meters away. A GRAY AREA.   (UPDATED) Addressing the issue of mayors jumping the vaccination line, President Rodrigo Duterte calls it a "gray area" as he thinks the said officials could've done it to show the vaccine is safe.   "If the purpose is to show to the constituency that it is safe, 'di ko maano masyado, there is a gray area there," Duterte says, remarking that some individuals even previously demanded him to be first in getting vaccinated.  It was earlier reported that five mayors got vaccinated against COVID-19 ahead of the prioritized sectors, with the DILG issuing show-cause orders. Tacloban City Mayor Alfred Romualdez, one of the involved officials, said he got inoculated to remove the people's fear of the vaccine.   Another local chief executive, Mayor Elanito Peña of Minglanilla, Cebu, confirmed that he received an AstraZeneca dose, despite protocols stating that healthcare workers, and not local officials, should be prioritized in the vaccine rollout.  Breaches in the priority line might jeopardize the Philippines' access to COVID-19 jabs supplied by the global COVAX facility, which has set strict guidelines for allocation. The World Health Organization has already cautioned the Philippines to respect the priority list for the vaccines obtained through the global vaccine sharing pool — or it might have no choice but to revisit the agreement. We beg you to help make this time of worldwide crisis due to COVID-19   a time of grace for ourselves, our family and others. Drawing inspiration from 16-year-old Swedish climate activist Greta Thunberg's Fridays for Future, a climate strike movement that started in 2018, the strike gathered thousands of students and adults who skipped school and work. Thunberg, in a speech in front of the strikers at Battery Park, called out politicians—their inaction and their "beautiful words"—for leaving the burden of the climate crisis to the youth. Filipinos from groups like Damayan Migrant Workers Organization, Ugnayan Youth, and Kabataan Alliance also joined the strike. Photos by Rey Anthony Ostria/Inquirer Southern Luzon
